When creating a patch for review in Crucible we are not able to identify the commit ID or who made the change. Even I tried creating a patch using "git format --patch ..." option oppose to git diff >path.txt. When submiting for review I cannot tell who made change or commit ID. If this is submitted and approved, when the user pushes the change how do we determine the pushed change has already been reviewed?
