The order of revisions added for a Light SCM review appears to be wrong.

From AccuRev (below)
-----
Here are the details of the issue we are facing:

The main idea of 'iterative review' is when we add file with some revision2 to existing review and that file is already exist in this review with revision1 we should gather all information about revisions. I implemented com.atlassian.crucible.scm.ChangelogBrowser interface and in method listChanges realized simple algorithm: call method com.atlassian.crucible.spi.services.ReviewService.getReviewDetails, retrieve all revisions of current file in existing review, and add them to the changset.

 

In the result, revisions are not sorted by FishEye server properly. For example, when I send versions 3,2,1 to FishEye it display 2,3,1. And next versions are added between last and first: 2,3,4,5,6,.....,1.

 

Please take a look at simple implementation of com.atlassian.crucible.scm.ChangelogBrowser interface in pseudo code:

public ChangeSets listChanges(Principal principal, String path, String oldestCsid, boolean includeOldest, String newestCsid,  boolean includeNewest, int maxChangesets) {

                // ---------------------//

                List<RevisionKey> revisionList = new ArrayList<RevisionKey>();

                String filePath = getPath(oldestCsid);

                String curVersion = getVersion(oldestCsid);

                String reviewID = getReviewID(oldestCsid);

                revisionList.add(new RevisionKey(filePath, curVersion));

                revisionList.addAll(getAllRevisionOfFileInCR(curVersion, reviewID));                  

   // ----------sort revisionList (newest is first) ---//

                ArrayList<ChangeSet> changeSet = new ArrayList<ChangeSet>();        

                changeSet.add(new ChangeSet(newestCsid, revisionList));

                ChangeSets changeSets = new ChangeSets(false, false, changeSet);

                return changeSets;

}

I noticed method listChanges always has same newestCsid, oldestCsid (they are equals) and maxChangesets (equal 1).
---------


From Geoff (below)
---------
fyi: this is how we determine (for light scm plugins) where it the list of revisions to insert new ones:

    public int getInsertIndex(List<CrucibleRevision> existingRevisions, CrucibleRevision fr, CrucibleRevision knownMax) throws SourceException {
        validateRevisionSource(fr);
        if (!existingRevisions.contains(fr)) {
            boolean needsAdd = true;

            int i = 0;
            for (CrucibleRevision currentRev : existingRevisions) {
                validateRevisionSource(currentRev);
                if ((fr.getCommitDate() != null && currentRev.getCommitDate() != null && fr.getCommitDate().before(currentRev.getCommitDate()))
                        || currentRev.equals(knownMax)) {
                    break;
                } else if (fr.getRevInfoKey().equals(currentRev.getRevInfoKey())) {
                    needsAdd = false;
                    break;
                }
                i++;
            }
            if (needsAdd) {
                return i;
            }
        }
        return -1;

